<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="416" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,1214,2001]" pageId="15" pageNumber="416">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,299,1214,1239]" pageId="15" pageNumber="416">Description:</emphasis>
Body length 
<quantity box="[455,523,1215,1239]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="15" pageNumber="416" unit="mm" value="8.0">8 mm</quantity>
, wing 
<quantity box="[601,670,1214,1239]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="15" pageNumber="416" unit="mm" value="5.0">5 mm</quantity>
. Palpus mostly black, white on outer face. Clypeus black with pale microsetulae. First flagellomere dark brown. Frontal vitta dark brown anteriorly. Fronto-orbital plates black and shiny. Postpronotal lobe black and shiny. Row of katepisternal setae brownish. Legs black. Hind femur narrowly white basally. Fore tarsus dark brown with gold/whitish pubescence ventrally at base of tarsomere one. Oviscape black and shiny, apex yellowish. Epandrium dark brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,1214,2001]" pageId="15" pageNumber="416">Head: Palpus broadened basally and gradually tapering to apex. Clypeus short, length less than half of width. First flagellomere covered by pale microsetulae. Two frontal setae. Paracephalon swollen and conical, extending beyond the vertex. Inner vertical setae inserted in strong tubercles. Vertex flattened. Supracervical line of setae black.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,1214,2001]" pageId="15" pageNumber="416">
Thorax: Mesonotum with white pruinosity. Notopleural setae strong. Posterior notopleural seta insertion slightly protuberant. Scutellum upturned, triangular. Femora with sparse brownish setulae. Mid and hind tibia flattened, sulcus on outer face very pronounced and curved (
<figureCitation box="[837,922,1610,1635]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–19" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1283,1306]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,193,1262]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[151,1436,193,1262]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 16–19. Cardiacephala aspera. 16, male and female, dorsal view; 17, female genitalia, ventral view; 18, male and female, Ecuador, Yasuni; 19, male genitalia, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1285306/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="416">Fig. 18</figureCitation>
). Wing with stigmatal and discal bands, apex clear with a dark and narrow preapical pigmentation. Crossvein r-m clear. R4+5 and M1+2 ending separately in wing margin. A1+CuA2 as long as CuA2. Female cervical sclerite slightly swollen at posterior end.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,1214,2001]" pageId="15" pageNumber="416">
Abdomen: Tergites with brownish setulae. Female abdomen: Oviscape with sparse pale microsetulae. Single spermathecal duct apically broad, ending in a cylindrical spermatheca (slightly damaged apically in 
<figureCitation box="[1263,1345,1760,1785]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–19" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1283,1306]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,193,1262]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[151,1436,193,1262]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 16–19. Cardiacephala aspera. 16, male and female, dorsal view; 17, female genitalia, ventral view; 18, male and female, Ecuador, Yasuni; 19, male genitalia, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1285306/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="416">Fig. 17</figureCitation>
). Paired spermathecal duct striate, delimited by a narrow basal half and a broader distal half with a ring-like swelling. Paired spermathecal duct stems thin and smooth, interrupted by a small rounded swelling and a small appendix. Paired spermathecae disc-shaped, flattened. Male abdomen: Ejaculatory apodeme bigger than epandrium and with a broad blade, wider than sperm pump. Phallapodeme extending to anterior limit of hypandrium. Distiphallus longer than epandrium but relatively short and thick, about three times as long as the phallic bulb (
<figureCitation box="[1335,1423,1940,1965]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–19" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1283,1306]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,193,1262]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[151,1436,193,1262]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 16–19. Cardiacephala aspera. 16, male and female, dorsal view; 17, female genitalia, ventral view; 18, male and female, Ecuador, Yasuni; 19, male genitalia, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1285306/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="416">Fig. 19</figureCitation>
). Distiphallus ending in a phallic bulb, phallic bulb subequal in length and width.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
