<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="417" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,1375,2012]" pageId="16" pageNumber="417">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,1951,1976]" pageId="16" pageNumber="417">Comments:</emphasis>
This Ecuadorian species is closely related to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ferro &amp; Marshall" authorityYear="2018" box="[850,980,1951,1976]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Cardiacephala" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="417" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lobulosa">
<emphasis box="[850,980,1951,1976]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="417">C. lobulosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[994,1088,1952,1975]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Cardiacephala" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="417" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigra">
<emphasis box="[994,1088,1952,1975]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="417">C. nigra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ferro &amp; Marshall" authorityYear="2018" box="[1143,1291,1951,1976]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Cardiacephala" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="417" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="velutinosa">
<emphasis box="[1143,1291,1951,1976]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="417">C. velutinosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, from which it differs by the swollen paracephalon and the disc-shaped, paired spermathecae.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
